<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	
	<!-- External style sheet link   ----- 1st Method -->
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="ducat.css">
<!-- External style sheet link   ----- 2nd Method  -->
<style>
	@import "ducat.css"
</style>
<title></title>
	<!-- Internal/Embedded Style -->
	<style>
		h2
		{
			background-color: aqua;
			border:4px solid red;
		
		}
	</style>
	
</head>
<body bgcolor=lightgrey>
<h1 align=center>Cascading Style Sheet</h1>
<h2> This is Heading2</h2>

<pre>
HTML- Structure/Layout of the webpage
Tags & Attributes

CSS-Cascading Style Sheet- 
Used to beautify the webpage elements for Look and feel
CSS1
CSS2
CSS3
property:value;
Note:-1) CSS is case sensitive and every property must be end by ;
		2)No space in between the CSS property words , use -

CSS Types-
1)Inline Style- It will be spefied in the same line of tag with style attribute in which you want to apply.
Note:- CSS property's value in Inline Style will be on priority

2)Internal Style/Embedded Style- It must be specified with style tag in head part

3)External Style File- Create a seperate .CSS file and specify the link in head part of HTML file



</pre>
